  "body": "**What happened**:\r\nWhen a CSI driver changes from attachable (`CSIDriver.spec.attachRequired`: true) to non-attachable (`attachRequired: false`) in the middle of attaching a volume, A/D controller still wants to attach the volume.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nA/D controller skips attach.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n1. Install CSI mock driver:\r\n    - With `--disable-attach=true`, so the mock driver does not require `ControllerPublish`)\r\n    - Without the external-attacher sidecar, so we can simulate slow attach.\r\n    - Without any CSIDriver instance, so A/D controller requires attach.\r\n2. Create a PVC and start a pod.\r\n3. Wait for time outs when attaching the provisioned volume, because the external-attacher is not running.\r\n4. Create CSIDriver with `attachRequired: false`.\r\n\r\nThe pod never starts. The volume is already in A/D controller desired state of world and nothing removes it from there.\r\n\r\nPod events:\r\n```\r\nSuccessfully assigned default/testpod to ip-10-0-160-231.us-east-2.compute.internal\r\nAttachVolume.Attach failed for volume \"pvc-1da1900a-7514-4a4a-9a65-bb54f5c42308\" : attachdetachment timeout for volume 5\r\nAttachVolume.FindAttachablePluginBySpec failed for volume \"pvc-1da1900a-7514-4a4a-9a65-bb54f5c42308\"\r\nUnable to attach or mount volumes: unmounted volumes=[vol], unattached volumes=[vol default-token-2mwq6]: timed out waiting for the condition\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.17.1\r\n\r\n/sig storage\r\ncc @gnufied @jingxu97 @msau42 ",
